  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Staff Nurse (Plastic Surgery)",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking an experienced Senior Staff Nurse for our Plastic Surgery Clinic. The ideal candidate will have a strong nursing background, with specialized experience in aesthetic procedures, to provide high-quality patient care and support clinic operations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Main Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Nursing or Equivalent with <strong>Advance Certificate in Perioperative Nursing</strong> is a must.</li>\n  <li>Valid Licence as a Registered Nurse (RN) under Singapore Nursing Board</li>\n  <li>at least 2-3 years in post registration clinical experience preferably in OR / AU / plastic surgery or cosmetic surgery setting.</li>\n  <li>With Certificate in Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS)/ Basic Life Support (BLS)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Strong understanding of surgical procedures, patient care, and post-operative care specific to plastic surgery.</li>\n  <li>Ability to manage multiple tasks, prioritize duties, and ensure a smooth workflow.</li>\n  <li>Assist the anaesthetist in all stages of administration of anaesthesia, provide pre- induction checks and assessment and close monitoring of patients’ post-induction, in accordance to established centre policies and procedures, standards of nursing care and practices.</li>\n  <li>Effective decision-making and problem-solving skills in high-pressure situations.</li>\n  <li>To respond and handle emergency situations in an efficient and calm manner, in code blue and other crisis.</li>\n  <li>To be responsible and accountable in handling and dispensing drugs and its administration, specially controlled drugs.</li>\n  <li>To be responsible and accurate nursing documentation in plato systems.</li>\n  <li>Assist in inventory control of AU consumables and maintenance of equipment.</li>\n  <li>To ensure customer satisfaction and follow through quality and service issues</li>\n  <li>Flexible and adaptable to changes</li>\n  <li>Assist in Filling insurance claims and Medisave and other document needed.</li>\n  <li>Sending a reminder to patient prior to surgery / consult / post-op.</li>\n  <li>Work with the Team of Aesthetic and Plastic surgery staff.</li>\n  <li>Computer savvy.</li>\n  <li>And other adhoc</li>\n</ul>",
